snippet.title: Amber Heard Hides Behind Her Hair At LAX
snippet.description: Wednesday, June 24, 2015 - Johnny Depp's wife Amber Heard returns to LA. Johnny Depp and Amber Heard are planning to boycott Australia following their clash with authorities after the actor brought his two dogs into the country. The Pirates of the Caribbean star was criticized by the minister for agriculture Barnaby Joyce and accused of breaking quarantine laws by bringing his pooches with him. Now, Amber has admitted the couple will be avoiding Australia and took a dig at the minister with a response, "I have a feeling we're going to avoid the land down under from now on, just as much as we can, thanks to certain politicians there."

snippet.title: Amber Heard Biography
snippet.description: Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American actress and model. Born and raised in Texas, Heard made her film debut in a minor supporting role in the sports drama Friday Night Lights (2004), followed by a series of other small roles in television and film. Her first leading role was in the horror film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006), but it was not released in the United States until 2013 due to distribution problems. Her second major role came in the short-running The CW television series Hidden Palms (2007).

Parenthood 5x06 "The M Word" - Sarah (Lauren Graham) and Amber (Mae Whitman) struggle with the wedding bell blues while Julia (Erika Christensen) and Joel (Sam Jaeger) try to keep it all together.
